  "text": "In this section, we extend our two-hop age results in (27), [CITATION_1] , and (30) to L hops. Considering an L-hop network, we have a single source node, n first hop receiver nodes, n 2 second hop receiver nodes and extending in this manner, n L end (L hop) nodes. The network model for L = 2 is shown in Fig. 1 and it is generalized such that each of n nodes of the first hop is tied to n further nodes making n 2 second hop nodes and similarly, each of these n 2 second hop nodes is further connected to n nodes forming n 3 end nodes, and so on, for L hops.",
